                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 1. Attach the filter basket to the portafilter." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "video":"IMG_8154.m4v" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 2. Set the filter below the grinder, and tap the handle once." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "img":"IMG_8155.JPG" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 3. It is normal for the portafilter to appear overfilled." }
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "img":"IMG_8156.JPG" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 4. Tamp the gound coffee down firmly using 30-40lbs of pressure." }
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "video":"IMG_8159.m4v" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 5. Insert the Portafilter underneath the group head, and rotate the handle towards the center." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "video":"IMG_8160.m4v" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 6. Press the 1 CPU button once to extract a single shot of expresso at the preset volume." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "img":"IMG_8161.JPG" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 7. The espresso will start flow after 4-7 seconds and should be the consistency of driping honey." }
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "img":"IMG_8162.JPG" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 8. Fill the jug with milk just below the \"V\" at the bottom of the spout." },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "video":"IMG_8163.m4v" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 9. Set the STEAM/HOT WATER dial to the STEAM position." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "video":"IMG_8171.m4v" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 10. With the milk spinning, slowly lower the jug to introduce air into the milk." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "video":"IMG_8166.m4v" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 11. Tap the jug on the table to collapse large bubbles." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
        {
            "elements":[
                { "template":"full", "video":"IMG_8167.m4v" },
                { "template":"caption", "markdown":"## 12. Pour milk directly into the expresso." },
                { "template":"play" },
            ]
        },
